{{Other uses|ICAR (disambiguation)}}
The '''Information Centre about Asylum and Refugees''' (ICAR) is an organisation involved in academic research and information provision on [[asylum seeker]]s and [[refugee]]s in the [[United Kingdom]]. Launched in 2000, ICAR was initially based at [[King's College London]].<ref name=About>{{cite web|url=http://www.icar.org.uk/2078/about-us/about-icar.html|title=About ICAR|publisher=Information Centre about Asylum and Refugees|accessdate=9 August 2010}}</ref> The organisation subsequently moved to [[City University London|City, University of London]] but, following withdrawal of support from City as a result of funding cuts,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://migrantsrights.org.uk/news/2010/information-centre-about-asylum-and-refugees-icar-faces-potential-closure|title=Information Centre about Asylum and Refugees (ICAR) faces potential closure|publisher=Migrants' Rights Network|date=7 June 2010|accessdate=9 August 2010}}</ref> it is now housed by the [[Runnymede Trust]].<ref name=Move>{{cite news|url=http://www.icar.org.uk/12428/icar-runnymede-trust/icar-runnymede.html|title=Statement from Neil Amas, Director of ICAR|publisher=ICAR|date=9 July 2010|accessdate=9 August 2010}}</ref>

