'''''Rembrandt: A Self-Portrait''''' is a 1954 American [[short film|short]] [[documentary film]] about the artist [[Rembrandt]] produced by [[Morrie Roizman]]. It was nominated for an [[Academy Award]] for [[Academy Award for Best Documentary (Short Subject)|Best Documentary Short]].<ref name="NY Times">{{cite web |url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/300252/Rembrandt-A-Self-Portrait/details |title=NY Times: Rembrandt: A Self-Portrait |accessdate=November 25, 2008|work=NY Times}}</ref>
This films shows a series of Rembrandt's artwork, including painting and drawings spanning his entire life and being shown as related of events throughout his life are narrated.
